{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01R4khTFLjFKK81v32oqzxwg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 25 tests pass. The three changes are complete:\n\n1. **Pre-threshold bilingual detection** — before threshold computation, suppresses the sole ALL_CAPS candidate (and any joins starting with it) from `scoredForThreshold` when a mixed-case pos-0 candidate exists. This prevents ALL_CAPS bonuses from inflating the threshold beyond the Polish/foreign-language title's reach.\n\n2. **Empty-pool fallback** — if threshold filtering discards all candidates, falls back to the best positional candidate from the full hard-filter-passing pool. Prevents sole valid candidates from being silently discarded by weak embedding differentiation.\n\n3. **Removed old post-threshold first-line protection** (the 12-line block at lines 457–479) — it was redundant (the pre-threshold fix handles the case more robustly) and was ineffective when the mixed-case title itself fell below threshold."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":284,"cache_read_input_tokens":54793,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":284},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fb15cb45-7bdf-4713-bb16-b0fca5051afe","uuid":"0c85365a-ad1f-4238-bdc2-5d80c18d7d2a"}
